{{Infobox football biography |name = Cameron Coxe |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Cameron Terry Coxe<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/news/2017/june/efl-club-retained-and-released-lists-published/ |title=EFL: Club retained and released lists published |publisher=English Football League |date=13 June 2017 |accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|12|18|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Cameron Coxe |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/cameron-coxe-256042/ |work=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=10 January 2018}}</ref> |birth_place = [[Merthyr Tydfil]], Wales |height = |position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] |currentclub = [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] |clubnumber = 36 |youthyears1 = 2005–2017 |youthclubs1 = [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] |years1 = 2017– |clubs1 = [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] |caps1 = 0 |goals1 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2014–2015 |nationalteam1 = [[Wales national under-17 football team|Wales U17]] |nationalcaps1 = 6 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2015–2016 |nationalteam2 = [[Wales national under-19 football team|Wales U19]] |nationalcaps2 = 6 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2017– |nationalteam3 = [[Wales national under-20 football team|Wales U20]] |nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |nationalyears4 = 2017– |nationalteam4 = [[Wales national under-21 football team|Wales U21]] |nationalcaps4 = 10 |nationalgoals4 = 0 |club-update = 14:22, 7 May 2017 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 05:31, 12 September 2018 (UTC) }} '''Cameron Terry Coxe''' (born 18 December 1998) is a Welsh professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Premier League | Premier League]] club [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].
==Early life== Coxe was born in [[Merthyr Tydfil]] and attended [[Afon Taf High School]].<ref name="WO">{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/cardiff-citys-20-best-players-9295093 |title=Cardiff City's 20 best players under 20: The hottest young talent the Bluebirds fans should keep an eye out for |publisher=WalesOnline |author=Terry Phillips |date=20 May 2015 |accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref>
==Club career== Coxe began his career at [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]], joining the club's youth academy at the age of seven before signing his first professional contract in February 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cardiffcityfc.co.uk/teams/u23-team/defender/cameron-coxe/ |title=Cameron Coxe |publisher=Cardiff City F.C. |accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/who-cameron-coxe-lowdown-cardiff-13515063 |title=Who is Cameron Coxe? The lowdown on Cardiff City's latest prospect and Neil Warnock's verdict on his Burton Albion debut |publisher=WalesOnline |author1 =Dominic Booth |author2 = Tim Coleman |date=23 August 2017 |accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref> He made his professional debut during a 2–1 defeat against [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]] in the second round of the [[EFL Cup]] on 22 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40932009 |title=Cardiff City 1–2 Burton Albion |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 August 2017 |accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref>
==International career== Coxe has represented Wales at [[Wales national under-19 football team|under-19]] level.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/son-former-bluebirds-legend-among-12574664 |title=Son of former Bluebirds legend among academy trio to be offered professional contracts with Cardiff City |publisher=WalesOnline |author=Ian Mitchelmore |date=8 February 2017 |accessdate=8 August 2017}}</ref> In May 2017, Coxe was named in the [[Wales national under-20 football team|Wales under-20]] squad for the [[2017 Toulon Tournament]]. After making his debut for the side in the tournament opener against [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/direct_festival_foot_uk.php?tournoi_id=15 |title=Wales U20 2–2 Cote D'Ivoire |publisher=Foot Espoirs |accessdate=23 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601021623/http://www.festival-foot-espoirs.com/direct_festival_foot_uk.php?tournoi_id=15# |archive-date=2017-06-01 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Coxe was named in the starting line-up in Wales' second group matche against [[France national under-20 football team|France]] but was left out of the final game against [[Bahrain national under-20 football team|Bahrain]] as Wales were eliminated in the group stage.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40100903 |title=Toulon Tournament: France U20 0-0 Wales U20 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2017 |accessdate=23 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40139643 |title=Toulon Tournament: Wales U20 1-0 Bahrain U20 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 August 2017}}</ref>
Coxe made his debut for the [[Wales national under-21 football team|under-21]] side on 1 September 2017 in a 3–0 victory over [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/09/01/europe/uefa-u21-championship/switzerland-under-21/wales-under-21/2429856/ |title=Switzerland U21 0–3 Wales U21 |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref> He was named in a preliminary senior [[Wales national football team|Wales]] squad in May 2018 for a friendly against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] but was left out of the final selection.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44136238|title=Hal Robson-Kanu not included in Wales squad for Mexico friendly |publisher=BBC Sport |date=20 May 2018|accessdate=21 May 2018}}</ref>
